==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Outshine
<hw>Out*shine"</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To surpass in
splendor, excellence, or achievement.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A throne of royal state, which far⟦br⟧
<qex>Outshone</qex> the wealth of Ormus and of Ind.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To shine more brightly than.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Outshoot</ent>⟦br⟧
